    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>CTC Sports of Farmington Hill, Michigan is a video production company that has long worked closely with the University of Michigan Athletic Department.  CTC has produced season highlight videos for football since 1988, for the 1992 and 1993 basketball teams and the 1986 NCAA champion hockey team,  as well as several special videos on Michigan football.  CTC also is producer of the in-season "Michigan Replay" television programs recappping each week's games and featuring the Michigan football and basketball coaches.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The collection includes football season highlight videos 1988-1993, special productions on Bo Schembechler's career and the Michigan - Ohio State football rivalry, the "Fab Five" basketball team's NCAA tournament second place teams of 1992 and 1993 and the 1995/96 NCAA champion hockey team.</p>
    </scopecontent>
